Lord Iqbal of the Waterfront Penthouses glanced sideways at the large, gilt mirror. Sideways because, he suspected that, despite all the stem cell lotion, he might struggle to set a maiden’s heart a-flutter. Still, he wanted reassurance, so he asked: “Mirror, mirror, on the wall, who is the wisest, most handsome, astute, sensitive, honest, medical genius philanthropic mogul of them all?” There was what sounded like a choking sound coming from the mirror. “Err… tis you, Your Magnificence…” Lord Iqbal shook his head in irritation: “How do I know you’re not just saying that?” “I am not, sire, and to prove...